This mod's reach extends beyond and further than the Populated series. Tired of dynamic spawn scripts crashing your game?

State.Description: Inigo is a fully voiced khajiit adventuring companion with over 7000 lines of unique dialogue - much of it about you. He'll level alongside you and avoid most traps. If you're sneaking he won't chatter and he'll whisper if you talk to him. He can run out of arrows. He's highly skilled in archery, one-handed, and sneak.
State.Name: INIGO

This new edition includes many improvements and additions, more compatibility, improved light sources, snow-covered lighposts and lanterns in snowy areas for a more immersive experience, all lanterns are moved by the wind and much much more........

State.Name: Fairies

State.Description:
This mod add new spells allows player to shoot a chain with a hook or spearhead on the end.

Thais spells is different type. One will pull target person or animal towards player and another will make player Lift up to Target distant.

Legend of Zelda Oracle of Seasons' Tarm Ruins mixed into Skyrim

This Quest is for Higher Level Characters, Lower Levels can give it a shot to see if they can do it.

State.Author: InsanitySorrow
State.Description: Lore Weapon Expansion (L.W.E) is a project that aims to expand the available weapons found in-game via loot and the crafting menu. All of the included weapons are lore based, meaning they are either based on designs found in previous games (with visual upgrades) or based on descriptions/places/characters mentioned in the series lore.
State.Name: Lore Weapon Expansion SE

State.Author: Foggypath
State.Description: Re-mastered/mixed 100% (4681 samples) of the original skyrim sound fx. Providing a smoother and plainer sound experience.No hum,no crackle,less masking,high definition low-end,no excessive high-end..and much more! Overall far more appealing to the ear..you'll hear things you've never heard before
State.Name: Lucidity Sound FX SSE

State.Author: Joseph Russell
State.Description: Lucien is a fully voiced Imperial follower with over 5000 lines of immersive, lore-friendly dialogue. Though he arrives in Skyrim as a cowardly scholar, he'll gradually gain strength and confidence by your side until he grows into a hero in his own right.
State.Name: Lucien - Immersive Fully Voiced Male Follower

State.Author: SarthesArai
State.Description: The complete SarthesArai map marker collection with DLC and OCS built in patch.
State.Name: Map Markers Complete with DLC and OCS

State.Author: Parapets
State.Description: Simplifies the creation of Mod Configuration Menus and extends them with powerful new features, such as persistent INI settings and hotkey registration. Mod authors will be able to write simpler, cleaner Papyrus scripts for their configs. Players will be able to spend less time in menus.
State.Name: MCM Helper

State.Author: Mrowr Purr
State.Description: Configuring MCMs has never been easier!
State.Name: MCM Recorder

State.Author: Soulmancer
State.Description: This is a patch that customizes Bellyache's New Dragons to be more unique and resourceful, fueled by custom spells, shouts and abilities from Enhanced Mighty Dragons
State.Name: Mighty Bellyaches New Dragon Species

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: A type of animated daedric armor set, created especially to protect the Sigil Stones that hold the Gates of Oblivion open, these golem-like constructs have 6 arms that deliver merciless, fiery blows.
State.Name: Aegis of the Sigil- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail Romanov - Stargatedalek - DiegoLPVA
State.Description: The Alfiq are the jolliest of Khajiit, having the size of a housecat but the heart of a lion--or a peacock! Extremely well-versed in magical arts, you may already have met one but just did not know it, thinking it one of your mewling kitty-cats that you feed milk and fish.
State.Name: Alfiq Spellcasters- Outlanders (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: On ancient ages, when neither the Blades had appeared yet, groups of annonymous honorable and strong men raised their weapons against the tyranny of dragons, when almost all still saw them as mighty gods to be venerated. This men are bound in destiny with dragons and with this last ones returning, their past slayers are coming back again too.
State.Name: Ancient Skeletons- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: This mod spreads around the world the bone remains of the countless species of animals that inhabit the vast province of Skyrim. Find from breathtaking skeletons of extinct giant snakes, long lost in the ocean, to fierce sabrecats bones buried in the ice, among many others.
State.Name: Animal Bones -Deepening Elements of Skyrim (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Add aggressive bats to your game by populating ruins, caves and tombs with this new variant.
State.Name: Enemy Bats - Mihail Monsters and Animals  (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The large Bolgans are a brutish ancient race, easily identified by their red skin and the heavy dwarven weapons and armor they carry. They once lived across all Skyrim, but when the nords arrived with thirst for conquest, the bolgan were decimated and almost extinct. The Dwemer saved them, in change for their services as soldiers.
State.Name: Bolgans- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Model and texture replacer for the vanilla low quality Bone Hawks, in addition to general improvements in their implementation.
State.Name: Bone Hawk Replacer- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail- SoN6of6TrediS- Amin Khani- ex0tekk
State.Description: The dark art of Necromancy holds many sources of immense power for those who go into it bravely enough to become true Necromasters. Among them, the transformation into a horrifying Bone Tyrant is perhaps the ability that offers greater physical power to a necromancer.
State.Name: Bone Tyrants- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Centaurs are an ancient and mysterious sentient beast-race, with traits of men and horse. Alternatively worshipped and despised, legends of their exploits range from the epic to the pornographic. The Council of Artaeum have called the Centaurs "true followers of the Old Ways" of Tamriel, but the true meaning of that is unknown.
State.Name: Centaurs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Curious birds with exuberant black plumage, crows are docile and fearless animals, enjoying living close to human civilizations for their own benefit, feeding on leftovers left by their inhabitants.
State.Name: Crows- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Minotaurs are a powerfull beast-race with physical features of both man and bull. The forest dweller cyrodilic ones are the most degenerated descendants of Morihaus and the now extinct Alessian Empire's minotaur civilization. This variant is feral, and bulkier than their Skyrim's cousins, but use more primitive armoury.
State.Name: Cyrodilic Minotaurs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail and Son6Of6Tredis
State.Description: Daedroths are large bipedal daedras of crocodylian appearance, and fearsome ferocity, that display considerable intelligence despite their look. Mostly found in the service of Molag and Dagon, these daedras can be encountered in different shapes and sizes according to their status, but always as formidable adversaries.
State.Name: Daedroths- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Add roaming exterior Draugr patrols to Skyrim with this mod. This patrols of undead merciless pillagers descend from their ancient nordic tombs into the roads at night, followed by their undead hounds, in search for clutter and fresh food to be used on their daily ritualistic dungeon tasks.
State.Name: Draugr Patrols - Mihail Monsters and Animals  (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail and Tasheni
State.Description: Two dark elf merchants do the pedlar job between Riften and Windhelm, serving the needs of the resident dunmers, but also the exotic tastes of some excentric nords.  Followed by their loyal Pack Guars, you will find a wide variety of products from the eccentric dark elf's land.
State.Name: Morrowind Merchants- Pedlars of Tamriel (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Durzogs, sometimes called sludgepuppies, are carnivorous animals not dissimilar to reptilian dogs. They have striped green scaly skin, six red eyes, spines on their back, head, legs and tail, and large teeth and claws designed for tearing. Durzogs are often domesticated by goblin tribes for hunting, guard and to fight on wars between clans.
State.Name: Durzogs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: An Elemental Triad is a type of golem created by the combination of the elements frost, lightning and fire. A result of Telvanni experiments back on Vvardenfell, this golem seems to be formed by the essences and parts of the bodies of storm, flame and frost atronachs.
State.Name: Elemental Triad- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Bone Colossi are large golem-like undead creatures made from bones assembled together and animated using powerfull Necromancy. They are raised from piles of bone matter by Bonemasters, and have small Bonelings as minions. The most powerfull Colossi are embedded in elemental magica, like fire, shock, or the powerfull coldharbour blue fire.
State.Name: Bone Colossus- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ettins are abominations with two-heads and an immense fury for all living beings. Descendants of an ogre tribe cursed by Malacath himself in remote ages, these tormented beasts of incredible strength, but limited intellect, are all that an adventurer does not want to encounter.
State.Name: Ettins - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Fire Golems are animated constructs molded from fiery stone, with explosive powers of the element fire, adorned with runic bracelets imbued with properties of magical condensing and containment.
State.Name: Fire Golem- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Created by the Fire Lords in the deep boilers of flaming lava in the realm of Infernace, these Flame Atronachs are true living storms of fire and igneous rock. Made in the image and likeness of the powerful Storm Atronachs, scholars claim that Flame Turmoils even surpass those in which they were inspired.
State.Name: Flame Turmoils- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ghosts are the spirits of the dead who have unfinished business on the mortal plane. They remain with human appearance and able to talk untill they start to lose self-identity, memories and purpouse, when they start to turn into just a moaner floating figure that does not look anything like a human would, and with visible signs of self-punishment.
State.Name: Classic Ghosts- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description:
First appeared on TES 1 Arena, Ghouls are olive colored small daedra who roam dungeons and feed on dead corpses. These creatures are usually encountered in tombs seeking aliment and they will attack intruders who enter their lairs. Although they are not intelligent, they have a natural 

cunning that aids them in finding carrion.
State.Name: Ghouls- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Usually secluded in remote camps in the icy mountains, or living in the faraway caves of the tribal clans, the female Giants are a rare but equally potentially fatal sight, as are their husbands.
State.Name: Giantesses- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Giant Rats are medium size aggressive rodents, they can be found in sewers, mines, ruined forts, abandoned buildings, halls of the dead and caves. They have no outstanding strengths, but they are known vectors of nasty diseases.
State.Name: Giant Rats- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Giant snakes are large and extremely poisonous reptiles, that occasionally eat small boats and were rarely seen on land. Widely hunted, today their numbers have reduced, and so have their size, but they are still dangerous enemies and the terror of any unwary adventurer, that they manage to ambush , with their slithering cunning.
State.Name: Giant Snakes - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: When a male giant child reaches a certain age, the old males bring him from the mountains into their mammoth camps to teach the youngling how to be an adult. This younglings are not as dangerous as an adult full grown male, but be aware, because they already can deal some serious damage and are very well protected by the adults.
State.Name: Giant Younglings- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Goblins are violent and primitive small orc-kin humanoids found throughout Tamriel, often living in sewers, caves, cluttered camps and ruins, in small clan-based societies. Accompanied by their tamed Durzogs, they are known for making their camps near roads to rob travelers. Goblins are sentient, and worship Malacath.
State.Name: Goblins- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Gorons are Nature Guardians, mountain spirits that take the form of yellow bulky humanoids made of rock. This large mountain-dwelling race is sligthly bigger than a regular man, but much stronger.  They are usually found protecting secluded caves and mountains all over Tamriel, often blending in with the rocks and catching trespassers unaware.
State.Name: Gorons- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Grahl is a member of the troll family, but besides that very little is known about them, some people also think they are just a myth. On ancient times they existed across all the province of Skyrim, but with the arrival of nords, giants, and other predators from Atmora, they were exiled into the remote snowy caves on the island of Solstheim.
State.Name: Grahl- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Griffin is a big flying apex predator native from High Rock, Hammerfell and Skyrim. He looks like a combination of a ferocious lion and a giant eagle. It usually inhabits primeval highlands and builds its nests on unreachable mountain summits, some also occur on the desert areas of Craglorn.
State.Name: Griffins- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Also known as Helhests, these mummified undead horses were the mounts of the ancient Norse, now resurrected by the same kind of power that keeps their former masters awake.
State.Name: Draugr Horse Mount- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: House Cats are docile small felines, used as pets by nords on the cities, also to make rodent control on farms and inns. They are ambient animals, and will not engage in combat.
State.Name: House Cats- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Imps are pesky small winged humanoids. Slightly intelligent, they can cast basic shock and fire spells in combat. Though bothersome by themselves, they are only especially dangerous in groups. Imps inhabit almost all the provinces of Tamriel, and are most commonly found around ruins, caves and dungeons, and are highly aggressive.
State.Name: Imps - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Indriks are feathered magical deer-like creatures that bear some direct relation to Y'ffre. Indriks fight using elemental-based attacks, with power drawn from the very Earth Bones beneath their hooves. Relentless protectors of nature, a wild Indrik will not hesitate to slaughter anyone he deems to be a potential danger to nature.
State.Name: Indrik- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Iron Golems are magical powerfull constructs created by those practiced in the arcane arts. These bulky beings are fashioned from iron to resemble a giant human form, then animated and set to particular tasks. Defeating one is a feat well worth praise, for this rusty iron titans are formidable opponents.
State.Name: Iron Golem -Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Mimics are one of the strangest daedra of Sheogorath. They disguise themselves as chests, waiting for victims to try to open them. When a victim attempts to do so, Mimics will proceed to reveal their dread true form and attack chomping her with their enormous mouth filled with pointed teeth and tearing skin with their long arms with sharp claws.
State.Name: Mimics- Mihail Monsters and Animas (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These ferocious men-bull descendants of Morihaus are said to have symbolized the Alessian Empire during the 1st Era, but later became commonly seen as dangerous beasts by other races. The variant that inhabits Skyrim is among those closest to the original glory and power of its race, unlike other more ferocious variants that live across Tamriel.
State.Name: Minotaurs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Few things are more pitiful than the transformation of a soul into an insane wraith. Among these, there are those who have plunged into a deep mental abyss of sadness and despair, becoming what many know as Mourning Souls, the personification of desolation.
State.Name: Mourning Souls- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Nixads are small and delicate insectoid-looking fairies that inhabit virtually all of Tamriel. These harmless and shy creatures occur in the most varied colors, which seem to be associated with the places where they inhabit.
State.Name: Nixads- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Pigeons are gentle, plump, small-billed birds with a skin saddle (cere) between the bill and forehead, that live commonly in human settlements, eating the remains of food, specially bread and grain, left behind by the city inhabitants.
State.Name: Pigeons- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Pixies are a type of Redcap, described as appearing as tiny, agile silhouettes formed from flickering shadows, or just as glimmering sparks, and with the personality of whimsical pranksters.
State.Name: Pixies- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Artificial creatures built from simple and mundane materials such as cloth, rope, buttons and pins, but imbued with the powerful and ominous Flame of Pestilence. These possessed ragdolls scare even the bravest of adventurers, used to confronting the most fearsome monsters.
State.Name: Ragdoll Golem- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Riekrs are a small species of blue snow goblins native to northern Skyrim and High Rock. Mischievous like their cousins from warmer regions, Riekrs live in trouble-making clans, plaguing nearby villages and travelers, always accompanied by their fierce Snowsnarl Durzogs.
State.Name: Riekrs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Rock Atronachs are a type of golem made of rock pieces covered and powered with ancient druidic runes painted on them, and animated by pure druidic magic, instead of a daedric/undead/nature spirit soul.
State.Name: Rock Atronachs-  Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail - Donutbomber - Blad3Zer0
State.Description: While many Toxin Doctors are dedicated to finding cures for the sick, and others remain neutral in their research with toxins inside their hidden laboratories, there are also those who dedicate their lives to cruelly poisoning their victims, using them on macabre experiments or for the simple fun of watching them agonize.
State.Name: Rogue Toxin Doctors- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Small and pesky lesser daedras, of little intelligence and cowardly behavior, with modest magical abilities, scamps and banekins should not be, at first sight, a matter of concern for prepared adventurers, however, in large numbers these two species can be a nuisance even for the most fearless warriors.
State.Name: Scamps and Banekins- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Thri-Kreen are mutated ritualistic warriors created by falmer alchemy using the Chaurus as a base. These obedient humanoid insects outperform the own Falmers in physical capacities, and do not need to rest, being excellent defenders of the hives where they live, despite having limited intelligence, just like any other Chaurus.
State.Name: Thri-Kreen Warriors - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: What could be more frightening than a vampire, than his bloody skeletal remains reanimated as irrational killing machines with an uncontrollable bloodlust? These fearless skeletons will freeze your spine when you find them patrolling the darkest of the dungeons.
State.Name: Skeletal Vampires- Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Wampas are giant carnivorous predatory reptomammals indigenous to the remote ice continent of Atmora, with up to 10 feet tall and over 400 pounds, covered in shaggy white fur constantly stained with the gore of slaughtered prey. They began to migrate to the north of Skyrim during the first period when the sea level dropped between both continents.
State.Name: Wampas - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Mihail and Son6Of6Tredis
State.Description: Watchers are floating tentacled daedra. They appear as giant floating eyeballs with multiple tendrils protruding from all sides. Users of powerfull magic, one must be carefull when fighting one of them, because their impredicable battle behaviour.
State.Name: Watchers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Wraiths are the last corruption phase of a soul bound to the mortal plane by unfinished business, when she no more has her memories and sense of self, but only pain, anger and guilt. In this stage, they are no more souls or ghosts, just hollow wraiths, remains of what one day was a person.
State.Name: Wraiths - Mihail Monsters and Animals (MIHAIL SSE PORT)

State.Author: Laup26
State.Description: Bard, Hunter, Big Game, Traveler and Knight Saddles for all explorers and adventurers. Get off your feet, take up the reins and aim for the horizon. Nothing can stop you when you and your trusty stead are ready for it all. More Saddles brings you four more saddles to further customize your horse for the journeys ahead.
State.Name: More Saddles SSE - Horse

State.Author: Ahzaab
State.Description: This mod brings some features from moreHUD into the inventory menu. From your inventory you can now see if enchantments are known by the player and other features. Also increases the Item Card size for mods that have long effect descriptions
State.Name: moreHUD Inventory Edition VR

State.Author: XxTWDxX
State.Description: Modifies the default death sounds of NPCs to make them sound more painful.
State.Name: More Painful NPC Death Sounds SE

Original.Name: Nether's Follower Framework - Universal Installer (LE or SSE)-55653-2-7-9-1631753067.zip

State.Author: Netherworks
State.Description: Nether's Follower Framework is a multi-follower system that is light on game resources and allows for up to 10 companions at one time. It provides a wealth of additional features, including immersion and quality-of-life functions to allow you to adventure with a small team of characters.
State.Name: Nether's Follower Framework

Original.Name: No Collision Between Actors SSE Edition-3469-1-0.7z

State.Author: TheNukaDude - original by KiCHo666
State.Description: No Collision Between Actors SSE Edition, FO4 port.
State.Name: No Collision Between Actors SSE

State.Author: Knight Life
State.Description: This is a grass fix for overgrown grass and grass clipping issues caused by grass mods adding grass to land textures that aren't suppose to have grass. It can be use to fix issues in areas that other mods do not fix. All options are light plugins (ESPFE/esl flagged) and can be added or removed at anytime.
State.Name: No Grassias - A Universal Grass Fix For Grass Mods

State.Author: dDefinder
State.Description:
This will simply remove the spinning around dance animation that they do before dying they will now just ragdoll when killed. Works for kills and dying from a high fall. It will not affect killmoves.



Includes the Removal of certain creature death pause animations
State.Name: No Spinning Death Animation SE

State.Author: Vanthryn
State.Description: This mod makes your character unstaggerable. This was made for VR version in mind but I am 99% sure it will work with regular Skyrim Special Edition as well. Compatible with Ordinator.
State.Name: No Stagger Mod

State.Author: Urtho
State.Description: Adds several wooden bridges across the northern marshlands of Hjaalmarch.
State.Name: Northern Marsh Bridges

State.Author: cuddy
State.Description: (Enemy) NPC mages get unfair advantages over the player in terms of magicka use and regeneration. This small mod aims to fix that.
State.Name: NPC mage balance fix

State.Author: moi
State.Description: NPCs are less like a sniper with arrows and bolts.
State.Name: Less Sniperlike NPCs

State.Author: Prog0111 SGSRules Wolfman5750
State.Description:
Onyx - VR Weathers is a weather mod based on Obsidian Weathers, then tweaked and adjusted to meet the needs of SkyrimVR.



All Screenshots are in VR!
